"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822849","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-01-23","<p>​We are aware of reports that Hizballah continues to amass an arsenal of weapons in Lebanon. The UK remains concerned about the threat that this poses to regional stability and the direct contravention of UN Security Council Resolutions 1559 and 1701. We will also continue to take action with the international community to encourage Iran to play a transparent and constructive role in regional affairs.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2018-01-23T17:53:23.667Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822849/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822849/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822849/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-01-15","Iran: Guided Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent reports he has received of the establishment of Iranian rocket factories in Lebanon under the control of Hezbollah.","false","Biography information for Paul Scully","Sutton and Cheam","Paul Scully","122532"
