ad with his counterpart in the US Administration on reports of an attack using chlorine gas in the Eastern Ghouta region of Syria on 13 January 2018.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","122630"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822948","Home Office","false","2018-01-22","<p>The Home Office and the National Crime Agency have initiated a SARs Reform Programme to deliver end-to-end improvements to the SARs regime. This will include improving the quality of SARs reporting, addressing concerns of defensive-reporting and under-reporting, enhancing the capabilities of the UK Financial Intelligence Unit, and increasing the use, exploitation and analysis of SARs by law enforcement bodies. The regulated sector have been extensively consulted and engaged in the design of the Reform Programme.</p><p>In addition, the Home Office’s ‘Flag It Up’ campaign works with the National Crime Agency and regulatory bodies in relevant professional sectors to drive engagement with best practice guidance on SARs reporting, and prevent potential involvement with money laundering activities. The NCA also engage on a regular basis with the regulated sector through the SARs Regime Committee.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-01-22T16:00:03.243Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822948/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822948/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822948/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-01-15","Money Laundering","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, pursuant to the Answer of 19 December 2017 to Question 118851, on Money Laundering, what steps he is taking within the reform to the SARs regime to drive up engagement with (a) Trust or Company Service Providers and (b) other reporting sectors on improvements to SAR reporting.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","122631"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822949","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-01-23","<p>We are concerned by the latest reports of an alleged Syrian regime chlorine attack in Eastern Ghouta on 13 January. UK officials are in regular contact with the Organisation for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons (OPCW), whose investigators are investigating the allegations of chlorine use in Eastern Ghouta, alongside a number of other allegations of chemical weapons use in Syria in the past year.</p><p>The OPCW-UN Joint Investigative Mechanism has found that the Asad regime has used chemical weapons on four occasions, and Daesh twice. The latest report from the OPCW Director General again states that Syria's Declaration of its chemical weapons programme required under the Chemical Weapons Convention remains incomplete, and that significant &quot;gaps, inconsistencies and discrepancies&quot; have not been resolved.</p><p>The British Government has made clear that it condemns the use of chemical weapons by anyone anywhere and that those who use chemical weapons should be held to account. I discuss on a regular basis the international community's response to the situation in Syria with international counterparts, including foreign ministers from the US and the EU, and have raised the matter with the Russian Foreign Minister. The UK continues to work closely with international partners to bring those in Syria responsible for the most atrocious crimes to account.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2018-01-23T14:30:32.627Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822949/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822949/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822949/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-01-15","Syria: Chemical Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with officials from the Organisation for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons on reports of an attack using chlorine gas in the Eastern Ghouta region of Syria on 13 January 2018; and what steps he plans to take to facilitate an investigation of such reports by the OPCW Fact-Finding Mission in Syria.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","122632"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822950","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-01-23","<p>The use of chemical weapons in Syria is a serious challenge facing the international community. The UK fully supports the Organisation for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons (OPCW) in its work to investigate cases of chemical weapons use, and to verify Syria’s Declaration of its chemical weapons programme under the Chemical Weapons Convention. As a member of the OPCW Executive Council, the UK has raised our concerns repeatedly and has called on Syria to comply with the Convention, for the illegal use of chemical weapons in Syria to stop immediately, and for those responsible to be held to account. We will continue to raise these issues in future meetings of the OPCW.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2018-01-23T14:32:37.993Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822950/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822950/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822950/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-01-15","Syria: Chemical Weapons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what plans he has to raise the use of chemical weapons by the Government of Syria at the 87th Session of the Executive Council of the Organisation for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons in March 2018.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","122633"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822951","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-01-22","<p>Companies House carries out systematic checks on all information received, ensuring that it is valid, complete and in compliance with company law filing requirements.</p><p> </p><p>Digital filings are subjected to a number of systematic checks. These help companies file the right information at the time of filing. It improves the quality of the information, and means that Companies House does not have to reject filings back to companies.</p><p> </p><p>Examiners employ similar checks for paper filings. Systematic checks and rules help ensure, among other things, that the specific document filed contains the correct company name and number, that the information filed is required by the legislation, that it is authenticated by the company.</p><p> </p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-01-22T11:36:47.817Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822951/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822951/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822951/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-01-15","Companies: Registration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answer of 20 December 2017 to Question 118852, on Money Laundering, how frequently and in relation to which comparative data are Companies House's systematic checks of the Companies Register conducted.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","122634"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822952","Home Office","false","2018-01-18","<p>No email correspondence dated 24 November 2017 has been received from the Hon Member.</p><p>The Wales and South West of England MPAM team contacted the Hon Member for Aberavon today and are now in receipt of the correspondence in question.</p><p>A response to the email correspondence will be issued to the Hon Member as soon as possible.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline  Nokes",,"2018-01-18T13:56:49.653Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822952/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822952/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822952/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-01-15","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, when she plans to respond to the email correspondence on an immigration case from the hon. Member for Aberavon dated 24 November 2017.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kinnock","Aberavon","Stephen Kinnock","122635"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822953","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-23","<p>The Royal Parks first expressed their support for locating the Holocaust Memorial in Victoria Tower Gardens at a meeting on 2 December 2015. The Parks’ support for the memorial in Victoria Tower Gardens was repeated in letters dated 15 March 2017, 7 April 2017 and 15 September 2017. Concerns were raised in these letters about the proposed learning centre. These letters have now been placed in the Library of the House.</p><p> </p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2018-01-23T17:58:03.77Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822953/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822953/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822953/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-15","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 22 November 2017 to Question 111729, on what dates Royal Parks expressed its support for locating in Victoria Tower Gardens (a) the Holocaust Memorial and (b) the Learning Centre; and if he will place in the Library copies of the communications from Royal Parks indicating that support.","true","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","122636"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822954","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-23","<p>Assessments of the number of visitors to the proposed Holocaust Memorial and Learning Centre are still being developed as part of the early stages of the design process. Full details will be published as part of the planning application.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler","122639","2018-01-23T17:59:17.77Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822954/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822954/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822954/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-15","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 12 December 2017 to Question 117268, on National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service, what conclusions the Government drew on visitor numbers to the proposed Holocaust Memorial and Learning Centre from its comparative assessment of visitor numbers to Holocaust memorials around the world; and if he will place a copy of that comparative assessment in the Library.","true","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","122637"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822955","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-01-19","<p>The UK and Overseas Territory Governments share a responsibility to the British citizens living in those territories to help enable them to lead secure, stable and more prosperous lives. The UK will remain party to the European Development Fund (EDF) until the closure of the 11<sup>th</sup> EDF, and we expect to confirm the arrangements for preserving the UK's Overseas Territories' EDF funding in the next phase of negotiations. After we leave the EU we will want to take our own decisions about how to deliver the policy objectives previously targeted by EU funding.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2018-01-19T14:15:30.07Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822955/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822955/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822955/answer","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822955/answer/previousversion/35208","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-01-15","British Overseas Territories","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the Government will match the level of EU funding provided to British Overseas Territories after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Anna McMorrin","Cardiff North","Anna McMorrin","122638"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822956","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-23","<p>Assessments of the number of visitors to the proposed Holocaust Memorial and Learning Centre are still being developed as part of the early stages of the design process. Full details will be published as part of the planning application.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler","122637","2018-01-23T17:59:17.833Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822956/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822956/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822956/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-15","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, pursuant to the Answer of 16 September 2017 to Question 106183, concerning the number of visitors to the proposed Holocaust Memorial, if he will place in the Library a copy of the assessment commissioned from Barker Langham.","true","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","122639"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822957","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-23","<p>A copy of the letter of 26 October 2015 from Lord Andrew Feldman to the then Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, the Rt Hon John Whittingdale, proposing that that the Holocaust Memorial be located in Victoria Tower Gardens has been placed in the Library of the House together with the Rt Hon John Whittingdale's reply.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2018-01-23T17:59:48.25Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822957/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822957/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822957/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-15","National Holocaust Memorial Centre and Learning Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, if he will place in the Library, a copy of the letter from Lord Feldman of October 2015 proposing that the Holocaust Memorial be located in Victoria Tower Gardens, and a copy of his Department’s response of November 2015.","true","Biography information for Sir Edward Leigh","Gainsborough","Sir Edward Leigh","122640"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822958","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-19","<p>The ‘learning framework’ referred to in Question 118847 covers a range of learning programmes for new recruits as well as professional development opportunities for current staff to support them to maintain, and grow, their skills and knowledge. Each learning programme and development opportunity will be tailored to provide specific skills for the role and tax regime. So the time spent, and the activity undertaken, will vary depending on the role and the individual’s own knowledge and experience.</p><p> </p><p>New recruits to tax roles have an induction programme which will be followed by technical and operational training which can take between 26 weeks and 30 months depending upon the level of specialist knowledge required. Current staff have a development plan which supports their ongoing professional development and provides at least 5 days each year to keep their skills up to date. The content of the development plan will be driven by the requirements of the tax regime and their particular role.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-01-19T13:58:05.567Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822958/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822958/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822958/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-15","Revenue and Customs: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the Answer of 20 December 2017 to Question 118847, what proportion of HM Revenue and Customs staff were engaged with their Learning Framework in the last 12 months; and which specialist areas those staff engaged with most frequently in that time period.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","122641"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822959","Scotland Office","false","2018-01-18","<p>My Department is in regular contact with other departments across Government, making representations on a wide range of matters with impact in Scotland. I have regular discussions with all my Cabinet colleagues about matters of importance to Scotland.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-01-18T16:42:43.94Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822959/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822959/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822959/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-01-15","Carillion: Insolvency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy on the effect of the liquidation of Carillion plc on jobs in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Jamie Stone","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Jamie Stone","122642"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822960","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-01-18","<p>All of the services directly provided to Service personnel and their families worldwide, including catering and housing, will remain unchanged; this has been communicated to Service personnel through the chain of command.</p><p>The facilities management contracts, which provide services to Service personnel and their families which involved Carillion, are all with Incorporated Joint Ventures (JVs). These are independent legal entities and the partners to those JVs are required to deliver the requirements of the JV if one of the partners fails.</p><p>We are working with the relevant JV partners to ensure that they continue to deliver the required services.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-01-18T16:03:51.183Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822960/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822960/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822960/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-01-15","Carillion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what support he will provide to those Scottish military sites which had planned to use Carillion facilities management contracts.","false","Biography information for Jamie Stone","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Jamie Stone","122643"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822961","Scotland Office","false","2018-01-18","<p>My Department is in regular contact with other departments across Government, making representations on a wide range of matters with impact in Scotland. I have regular discussions with all my Cabinet colleagues about matters of importance to Scotland.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2018-01-18T16:42:43.987Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822961/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822961/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/822961/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2018-01-15","Military Bases: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Defence on finding a replacement organisation for facilities management of those military sites in Scotland which were due to be under Carillion facilities management.","false","Biography information for Jamie Stone","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Jamie Stone","122644"
