"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823046","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-01-23","<p>Different organisations have a range of responsibilities for training and development. Individual employers have responsibility for supporting staff with courses which are required to fulfil duties to work in their organisation and core employment requirements.</p><p> </p><p>National funding through Health Education England (HEE) has historically been used to support development of the National Health Service workforce. HEE invests up to £300 million per year on supporting individuals in NHS employment achieve registered qualifications and a further £80 million on workforce transformation projects agreed locally, some of which has prioritised training courses for ongoing development.</p><p> </p><p>HEE is considering alternative models for traditional continual professional development funding; for example exploring routes for apprenticeships for post graduate qualifications that previously may have been funded directly at a national level.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-01-23T17:28:42.423Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823046/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823046/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823046/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-01-15","NHS: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, if he will take steps to improve the opportunities for NHS staff to receive on-going education and training; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","122729"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823047","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-01-23","<p>We strongly condemn all violations of the Cessation of Hostilities in South Sudan. We call on all signatories to the agreement to end all violence immediately and to enter the next round of the High Level Revitalisation forum with a genuine commitment to making progress. We are urging the Intergovernmental Authority on Development to ensure that the consequences for those who seek to spoil the peace process, or violate any agreement, are clearly communicated and effectively implemented.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2018-01-23T17:12:37.323Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823047/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823047/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823047/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-01-15","South Sudan: Peace Negotiations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps he plans to take as a result of reported violations of the South Sudan cessation of hostilities agreement.","false","Biography information for Sir Henry Bellingham","North West Norfolk","Sir Henry Bellingham","122730"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823048","Department for Transport","false","2018-01-22","<p>The number of ships detained by Maritime and Coastguard Agency inspectors for breaches of Standards in Title 2, Conditions of Employment in the Maritime Labour Convention (MLC) 2006, since August 2014, when the MLC came into force in the UK, for ships registered to countries on the Paris MoU White List is shown below, with their flag of registry:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Type of vessel</p></td><td><p>Number Detained</p></td><td><p>Flag(s)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Chemical tanker</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>-</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Oil tanker</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>Marshall Islands</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Offshore supply vessel</p></td><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>Marshall Islands</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Bulk carrier</p></td><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>Marshall Islands (3)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Passenger ship</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>-</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Roll-on roll-off passenger ship</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>-</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>General cargo ship</p></td><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>Panama (5), Malta (1)</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani","122725 ; 122726 ; 122727 ; 122728","2018-01-22T14:44:45.29Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823048/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823048/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823048/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-01-15","Shipping: Conditions of Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many (a) chemical and (b) oil tankers registered on the Paris MoU on Port State Control’s White List have been detained by Maritime and Coastguard Agency inspectors for breaches of Standards in Title 2, Conditions of Employment in the Maritime Labour Convention, to date; and under what flag each such vessel was registered.","false","Biography information for Pau