"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823101","Cabinet Office","false","2018-02-26","<p>Individual departments are responsible for putting in place arrangements for telephony services and helplines. There is not specific central guidance in place for hold facilities on Government phone services.</p>","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden",,"2018-02-26T17:17:25.323Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823101/answer","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823101/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/823101/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-01-15","Government Departments: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, by what means Departments select hold music for Government telephone services.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","122784"
