clared as surplus to NHS needs in (a) West Sussex and (b) the Coast to Capital local enterprise partnership area.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","122440"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821523","Department for Transport","false","2018-01-22","<p>A preliminary recommendation from the technical group on glare, in which my officials participate, was presented to the UN Expert Group on Lighting in October 2017. Under scrutiny, concerns have been raised, including by the UK, that the recommendation may not adequately address the glare problem. Further evidence was requested which the Department expects to be presented when the subject is discussed again in April 2018.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2018-01-22T11:49:14.513Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821523/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821523/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821523/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-01-12","Motor Vehicles: Lighting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress is being made on his Department's work leading a glare group as part of the UN expert group on vehicle lighting.","false","Biography information for Alex Chalk","Cheltenham","Alex Chalk","122441"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821524","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-01-17","<p>I continue to monitor the implementation of the Defence Recruitment Process closely and can confirm that an agreed remediation plan is in place that will see updates to the system occurring through to the end of February 2018. The most pressing defects have been prioritised and a significant number have already been addressed. All Services have implemented Business Continuity Plans to maintain an active recruitment pipeline.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-01-17T17:40:43.917Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821524/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821524/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821524/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-01-12","Armed Forces: Recruitment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 11 January 2018 to Question 121442, on Armed Forces: Recruitment, when those system defects will be fixed; and what assessment he has made of the effect of those defects on recruitment.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","122442"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821525","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-17","<p>The Government 's expectations for the minimum threshold for the pooling assets under the local government pension scheme, and a summary of the evidence taken into account when setting that threshold, are set out in the 'Local Government Pension Scheme: Investment reform criteria and guidance' (November 2015).</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2018-01-17T16:59:07.59Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821525/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821525/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821525/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-12","Local Government Pension Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, when he plans to publish the evidence used to calculate the minimum threshold for pooling assets under the local government pension scheme.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","122443"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821526","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-17","<p>The Government continues to believe that investment pools of at least £25 billion are required to deliver the full potential for reduced costs in the local government pension scheme. However, the Government has accepted that the Welsh pool, established by, and for the Welsh pension funds, is in a special position, taking account of the possibility of eventual devolution.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2018-01-17T16:55:06.55Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821526/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821526/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821526/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-12","Local Government Pension Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government for what reasons the scale criteria of £25 billion for pooling local government pension scheme assets has been dropped; and what evidence was used to inform the lowering of that threshold.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","122444"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821527","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-17","<p>The final proposals for the development of the pools in July 2016 estimated set up costs excluding transition of assets of around £20 million, and initial running costs of around £11 million per annum, in order to achieve estimated total net savings of £1-2 billion by 2033. The costs of establishing each pool in the local government pension scheme, and future costs, will be met by the participating funds and will be published in the annual reports of the pools.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2018-01-17T16:56:18.757Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821527/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821527/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821527/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-12","Local Government Pension Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government what the cost to the public purse of establishing each local government pension scheme pool has been to date; and what costs to the public purse his Department has forecast for each local government pension scheme pool in each year until 2020.","false","Biography information for Peter Dowd","Bootle","Peter Dowd","122445"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821529","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-22","<p>Ministers and officials meet regularly with representatives of Northamptonshire County Council, and all councils, across the full range of policy areas covered by the department.</p><p>In relation to the financial position of the Council, officials have had monthly phone calls with Council officers, and the Secretary of State met with the Leader of the Council most recently on 12 October 2017.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2018-01-22T17:07:31.147Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821529/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821529/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821529/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-12","Northamptonshire County Council","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what meetings held by (a) Ministers of his Department and (b) officials of his Department have had with representatives from Northamptonshire County Council from 1 January 2017 to date.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","122447"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821530","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-22","<p>On 21 December 2017 the Government published its response to the consultation on ‘ Tackling unfair practices in the leasehold market’. This set out a range of measures to cut out unfair and abusive practices within the leasehold system, including introducing legislation to prohibit the development of new build leasehold houses, other than in exceptional circumstances; and restricting ground rents in newly established leases of houses and flats to a peppercorn (zero financial value).</p><p>For existing leaseholders, the Government wants to see developer compensation schemes going further and faster, with support extended to all those with onerous ground rents, including second hand buyers and for customers to be proactively contacted. We will be keeping a close eye on progress and will consider measures that could be pursued to take action if necessary. We have also set out work with the Law Commission to make buying a freehold or extending a lease easier, faster, fairer and cheaper.</p>","Esher and Walton","Dominic Raab","122451 ; 122453","2018-01-22T17:57:48.06Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821530/answer","Biography information for Dominic Raab","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821530/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821530/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-12","Ground Rent: Leasehold","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what steps his Department is taking to prevent rises in leasehold ground rents.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","122448"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821531","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-01-22","<p>The situation in Northamptonshire has been developing for some time. However as a result of recent documentation from the external auditor and the Local Government Association, as well as the council’s own publicly available budget documents, it is now appropriate to take a detailed view of the authority to ascertain its compliance with its best value duty.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2018-01-22T16:59:29.67Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821531/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821531/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821531/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-01-12","Northamptonshire County Council","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, when and by whom he was first informed of the financial difficulties at Northamptonshire County Council.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","122449"
