"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821565","Wales Office","false","2018-01-18","<p>None. The Wales Office does not own or lease any vehicles.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2018-01-18T13:20:35.037Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821565/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821565/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821565/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2018-01-12","Wales Office: Electric Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, how many vehicles in his Department's fleet are (a) electric vehicles and (b) ultra-low emission vehicles.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","122483"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821566","Northern Ireland Office","false","2018-01-22","<p>My Department holds two cars as part of fleet arrangements; neither are electric or ultra- low emissions vehicles.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2018-01-22T16:38:47.41Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821566/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821566/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821566/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2018-01-12","Northern Ireland Office: Electric Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many vehicles in her Department's fleet are (a) electric vehicles and (b) ultra-low emission vehicles.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","122484"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821567","Department for International Trade","false","2018-01-23","<p>The Department for International Trade uses the Government Car Service for vehicle provision. Cars provided to Departments by the Government Car Service will be included in the return for the Department for Transport.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2018-01-23T10:18:32.447Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821567/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821567/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821567/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-01-12","Department for International Trade: Electric Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many vehicles in his Department's fleet are (a) electric vehicles and (b) ultra-low emission vehicles.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","122485"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821568","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-01-22","<p>The Department of Digital, Culture, Media and Sport does not own any vehicles.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2018-01-22T15:45:06.137Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821568/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821568/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821568/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-01-12","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport: Electric Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many vehicles in his Department's fleet are (a) electric vehicles and (b) ultra-low emission vehicles.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","122486"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821569","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-22","<p>Section 100A of the Customs and Excise Management Act 1979 (CEMA) provides the legal basis for the designation of free zones by HM Treasury and will continue to do so following UK withdrawal from the EU. Applying for designation as a free zone will be a commercial decision to be taken by private port operators.</p>","Central Devon","Mel Stride",,"2018-01-22T14:46:48.073Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821569/answer","Biography information for Mel Stride","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821569/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821569/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-12","Free Zones","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether British ports will be designated as free ports after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Luke Pollard","Plymouth, Sutton and Devonport","Luke Pollard","122487"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821570","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-19","<p>HM Treasury recognises the important role data and transparency play in ensuring the accurate pricing of climate-related financial risk. That is why the government has officially endorsed the recommendations of the Task Force on Climate-related Financial Disclosures (TCFD) and encouraged publicly listed firms to implement them, in line with the TCFD’s voluntary approach.</p><p> </p><p>To support this, the private sector Green Finance Taskforce, which was launched by HM Treasury and the Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, has also been asked to consider if government should and could play a role in enabling and facilitating the implementation of the TCFD recommendations. The implementation of the TCFD recommendations is a cross-cutting workstream of the Green Finance Taskforce, the Terms of Reference of which can be found here: https://www.gov.uk/guidance/green-finance</p><p> </p><p>Participants from across the financial services industry have given feedback on implementing the recommendations, including potential government action to encourage uptake. The Taskforce’s report is due to be published in spring 2018 and will include TCFD-related considerations.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen",,"2018-01-19T12:55:36.657Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821570/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821570/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821570/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-12","Companies: Climate Change","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what progress his Department has made on encouraging companies to take up the recommendations of the Task Force on Climate-related Financial Disclosures.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","122488"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821571","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-01-18","<p>It is for The Pensions Regulator (TPR) to decide what action it will take following the publication of the updated UK Stewardship Code by the Financial Reporting Council (FRC). TPR consider revisions to its guidance as a part of its ongoing guidance review, while taking account of its statutory objectives including to protect member benefits and promote good administration of pension schemes.</p>","Hexham","Guy Opperman",,"2018-01-18T13:04:56.257Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821571/answer","Biography information for Guy Opperman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821571/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821571/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-01-12","Company Accounts: Occupational Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what plans his Department has to update the advice of The Pensions Regulator when the Financial Reporting Council publishes its reviewed UK Stewardship Code in 2018.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","122489"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821572","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-01-19","<p>The Department for Exiting the European Union is undertaking a comprehensive programme of analytical work across a range of scenarios. We are examining all areas of the UK economy from a number of perspectives and seeking input from a wide range of stakeholders. As part of this, we have looked at 58 sectors of the economy, as set out in our response to the Lords EU External Affairs Sub-committee report “Brexit: Trade in Goods” which can be found at: <a href="https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld201617/ldselect/ldeucom/129/129.pdf" target="_blank">https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld201617/ldselect/ldeucom/129/129.pdf</a>.</p><p> </p><p>We will continue to engage with businesses and industry bodies from all sectors of the economy, and all regions and nations of the UK, in order to inform our negotiations with the EU.</p><p> </p><p>We have published 14 detailed papers on the negotiations to date and will continue to be as open as possible subject to the overwhelming national interest of preserving our negotiating position. Ministers have a specific responsibility, which Parliament has endorsed, not to release information that would undermine our negotiating position.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","122058 ; 122059 ; 122352 ; 122361 ; 123126 ; 123129","2018-01-19T16:18:35.93Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821572/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821572/answer","Brexit- trade in goods.pdf","Brexit- trade in goods.pdf","Brexit: Trade in Goods","Brexit: Trade in Goods","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821572/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-01-12","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, if he will list the titles of all assessments undertaken by his Department's Market Access team on the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","122490"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821573","HM Treasury","false","2018-01-22","<p>The European Investment Bank, and its offshoot, the European Investment Fund, provide financing for infrastructure investment and growth businesses in a range of sectors including renewable energy.</p><p> </p><p>As set out in the joint report on progress during phase 1 of the negotiations, the government considers that there could be mutual benefit from a continuing arrangement between the UK and the EIB, and wishes to explore these possible arrangements in the second phase of negotiations.</p><p> </p><p>The government is also continuing to take steps to ensure that finance continues to be available for good infrastructure projects and growth businesses: the UK Guarantees Scheme, which gives government support for private infrastructure finance, has been broadened to offer construction guarantees, and at Budget the Chancellor launched the Charging Infrastructure Investment Fund to support the transition to zero emission vehicles.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2018-01-22T15:54:53.54Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821573/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821573/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/821573/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-01-12","European Investment Bank","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, how does his Department plan to replace European Investment Bank (EIB) investment in the UK after the UK has left the EU; and what assessment his Department has made of the effect of EIB funding on the UK's green industry.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","122491"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820596","Women and Equalities","false","2018-01-11"," The Government is committed to helping men and women to balance work and childcare between them. It is good for parents and children, as well as being an important way to address the Gender Pay Gap. Shared Parental Leave and the right to request flexible working enables parents to arrange work and care in a way that works for them. ","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins",,"2018-01-11T11:57:10.777Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820596/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820596/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820596/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2018-01-11","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","What steps the Government is taking to help (a) women and (b) men balance work with childcare responsibilities.","false","Biography information for Eddie Hughes","Walsall North","Eddie Hughes","903244"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820656","Cabinet Office","false","2018-01-22","<p>There is no firm guidance on this matter as each consultation is different; some will make a call for evidence on a topic and others will seek views on the details of a new Government policy. The Consultation Principles (copy attached), which are published on Gov.uk, stress the importance of targeting consultations at a full range of people, businesses and voluntary bodies affected by the policy. The guidance notes that departments should consider targeting specific groups and ensure they are aware of the consultation and can access it.</p>",,"Lord Young of Cookham",,"2018-01-22T14:02:37.217Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820656/answer","Biography information for Lord Young of Cookham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820656/answer","Consultation Principles 2016 .pdf","Consultation Principles 2016 .pdf","Consultation Principles 2016 ","Consultation Principles 2016 ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820656/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2018-01-11","Public Consultation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what guidance is made available to Ministers regarding the need to maintain, and appear to maintain, an open mind during Government policy consultations.","false","Biography information for Earl Attlee",,"Earl Attlee","HL4626"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820657","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-01-22","<p>The Financial Reporting Council (FRC) is funded through a combination of statutory and voluntary funding arrangements. The FRC consults stakeholders annually on the amounts requested under these arrangements. Requests from the Financial Reporting Council for voluntary payments explain that the payments are non-statutory and voluntary. The Financial Reporting Council also explains to funders that, should the system of voluntary payments prove unsustainable, they would request that the Secretary of State make regulations to put the funding requirements on a statutory basis. The Companies (Audit, Investigations and Community Enterprise) Act 2004 includes provisions to enable this.</p>",,"Lord Henley",,"2018-01-22T11:47:35.93Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820657/answer","Biography information for Lord Henley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820657/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820657/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-01-11","Financial Reporting Council","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government why companies, pension funds and taxpayer-funded public bodies are served notices by the Financial Reporting Council requesting payment for a charge described as a levy without any accompanying statement that the charge does not have the status of levy or tax, and is not actually required to be paid.","false","Biography information for Baroness Bowles of Berkhamsted",,"Baroness Bowles of Berkhamsted","HL4627"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820658","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-01-22","<p>The Financial Reporting Council operates an office in Brussels in order to support its work as the designated competent authority for audit in the UK and on accounting regulation. The then Department for Business, Innovation and Skills was informed of the decision to open the office when it was established.</p><p> </p><p>Up until December 2014 the Financial Reporting Council’s status as a public body within central government was pending review by the Office of National Statistics. The Brussels office was established in 2012.</p>",,"Lord Henley",,"2018-01-22T11:46:36.177Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820658/answer","Biography information for Lord Henley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820658/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820658/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-01-11","Financial Reporting Council","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether the opening of an office in Brussels by the Financial Reporting Council for lobbying activity was authorised by the Cabinet Office as required by the restrictions placed on non-departmental public bodies by the rules set by the Cabinet Office; and if so, when.","false","Biography information for Baroness Bowles of Berkhamsted",,"Baroness Bowles of Berkhamsted","HL4628"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820659","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-01-22","<p>The Financial Reporting Council (FRC) has an established code of conduct which applies to FRC staff to ensure that conflicts of interest and any other associated threats to independence are managed appropriately. In addition, the FRC applies, on a case-by-case basis measures to ensure that any potential conflicts arising from a proposed departure from the FRC to another organisation are managed.</p><p> </p><p>The Government has made no assessment of this policy.</p>",,"Lord Henley",,"2018-01-22T11:45:22.247Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820659/answer","Biography information for Lord Henley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820659/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/820659/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-01-11","Financial Reporting Council","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what assessment they have made of the extent to which transfers of staff from the Financial Reporting Council to (1) the International Accounting Standards Board, (2) large accounting firms, and (3) other organisations, have complied with the restrictions on appointment of public officials into private sector roles.","false","Biography information for Baroness Bowles of Berkhamsted",,"Baroness Bowles of Berkhamsted","HL4629"
